---

<section class="bg-paper text-plum-darkest py-12 md:py-16">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.2fr] gap-10 lg:gap-14 items-center">
      <div
        class="aspect-[4/3] rounded-3xl bg-teal/80 flex items-center justify-center p-10"
      >
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center text-center gap-4">
          <svg
            width="72"
            height="72"
            viewBox="0 0 64 64"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#25101d"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            aria-hidden="true"
          >
            <polygon points="32 6 54 19 54 45 32 58 10 45 10 19 32 6" />
            <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="5" />
            <circle cx="22" cy="24" r="2" />
            <circle cx="42" cy="40" r="2" />
            <path d="M27 28l-5 -4" />
            <path d="M37 36l5 4" />
          </svg>
          <p
            class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-plum-darkest leading-tight tracking-wider"
          >
            QUANTUM<br />BIOLOGY<br />INSTITUTE
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6">
          The Quantum Biology Institute
        </h2>
        <div
          class="space-y-5 font-sans text-base text-plum-darkest/80 leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            To push this work forward, we made a major grant to the Quantum
            Biology Institute, a nonprofit lab based in Los Angeles. This is
            the largest grant ever awarded in quantum biology, and it's funding
            real scientists doing real experiments.
          </p>
          <p>
            With this support, the Institute is building custom lab equipment,
            including a quantum microscope designed to detect electron spin
            states inside live cells. They'll use that tool to investigate
            whether biology actually depends on quantum effects, and if so, how
            we can detect, influence, and eventually control them.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
